article.headline: Pacific 77, Cal St.-Fullerton 62
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Chad Troyer scored 17 points to lead Pacific to a 77-62 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Saturday. Michael Kirby and Bryan LeDuc added 12 ponts apiece for the Tigers (10-6, 3-2 Big West). Josh Akognon scored 17 points for the Titans (8-10, 2-4) who have lost four of six. Chris Rhymes added a career-high 13 points. Pacific shot 58.3 percent in the first half in building a 36-22 halftime lead. The 22 points were the fewest Fullerton had scored in any first half this season. Akognon's 3-point shot 12 seconds into the second half narrowed the Titans' deficit to 36-25. Pacific shot 68 percent in the second half and led by as many as 26 points.
